        <page n="02" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.04.17.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>The End of the Republican Party</head>
                <origin>Plattsburg N.Y. Republican</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Was there ever, we ask, such a shameless abandonment, by a party, of its
                    principles under the color of which it rode into power."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Complains that the Republican party failed to uphold its principles and
                    avert the disunion crisis.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>$53,000,000 Idle!</head>
                <origin>N.Y. Express</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Civil war is fatal to commerce and enterprise."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>N.Y. Express</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Bemoans the fact that $53,000,000 is sitting idle in banks instead of being
                    used for investment, owing to the uncertain future of the country.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Fiction and anecdotes</pageNote>
        </page>
